title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
OB: When calling the 'getcolumnlabel' function before data extraction, the labels returned are null. However, after data extraction, the labels are recognizable strings.
EB: Bug 121170 - When calling the 'getcolumnlabel' function from the meta data object, it should return user recognizable strings. This is important because the labels need to be displayed to the end user before extraction. Therefore, the 'getcolumnlabel' function should return the same labels both before and after extraction.
